          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1618242080799-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1618242080799-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1618242080799-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cornflour</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to a large bowl and stir in 60ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[80ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> until you are left with a smooth batter</p><p>Cut your <strong>cauliflower</strong> into small florets, then add the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong> to the <strong>batter</strong> and stir until they are evenly coated</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 pans!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
